abstract = {To address the challenges of cultural differences in globalization and meet the demand for cross-cultural talents from international enterprises, a questionnaire was administered to university faculty, students, and corporate HR professionals. Data was collected and modeled using the random forest algorithm to explore the value of integrating AI with a cross-cultural perspective. It was found that AI significantly empowers cross-cultural assessment and personalized training, while the cross-cultural perspective enhances relevance. A “AI + Cross-Culture” training model is proposed, offering a reference for universities to optimize their systems and align with international demands.},
